     __________________________________________________________________

     * Clean Cities is a program by the U.S. Department of Energy that is
       designed to encourage the use of alternative fuel vehicles (AFVs)
       and their supporting infrastructure throughout the nation. In
       Southern California, the Clean Cities program is being coordinated
       by SCAG.  For further information, contact Marnie Tenden at (909)
       396-5757 or by e mail at MarnTen@aol.com
     * 2001 Regional Transportation Plan (RTP) Update Final Program
       Environmental Impact Report (PEIR) Notice of Determination (NOD)
       Note: The 2001 RTP Final Program Environmental Impact Report was
       certified by SCAG's Regional Council on April 12, 2001. For further
       information, please contact Rich Macias at (213) 236-1805 or by e
       mail at macias@scag.ca.gov
     * Draft 2001 Regional Transportation Plan (RTP) Update Program
       Environmental Impact Report (PEIR)
     * Plan Regional de Transporte 2001 (RTP, siglas en ingles)
       Actualizacion de Informe de Programa de Impactos Ambientales (PEIR)
       Resumen Ejecutivo
     * 2001 Regional Transportation Plan (RTP) Update Program
       Environmental Impact Report (PEIR) Notice of Preparation (NOP)
     * Plan Regional de Transporte 2001 (RTP, siglas en ingles)
       Actualizacion de Informe de Programa de Impactos Ambientales (PEIR)
       Aviso de Preparacion
     * Final 2001 Regional Transportation Improvement Program (RTIP)
       Note: The 2001 RTIP was federally approved on September 25, 2001.
       For further information contact Valerie Gibson at
       gibson@scag.ca.gov.
       -  Executive Summary (Volume I of III)
       -  Technical Appendix (Volume II of III)
       -  Project Listing (Volume III of III)
     * The Regional Comprehensive Plan and Guide is a thirteen chapter
       road map for development and quality of life in Southern
       California.
     * Housing Southern Californians (Regional Housing Needs Assessment)
     * 2001 Travel and Congestion Survey
     * California Maglev Deployment Program:  Bringing High-Speed Travel
       to Southern California


